xml

Class RequirementsInterchangeFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • xml.RequirementsInterchangeFormat
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRequirementAnalysis, IXMLFormat

    public class RequirementsInterchangeFormat
extends java.lang.Object
implements IXMLFormat
    A JAXB conform requirement analysis format to store the data in a XML file. The Requirements Interchange Format was created by the Object Management Group and is a format to format XML files with requirement analysis data. The RequirementsInterchangeFormat is not implemented in this version, because of lack of time.
    See Also:
    www.omg.org/spec/ReqIF/
